<h2><span id="Question:_I’m_using_Case_Exchange_to_exchange_Incidents_with_an_external_system._Agents_with_the_‘Tenant_Admin’_role_can_see_the_information_on_the_exchanged_Incident,_but_other_users_can_not._How_do_I_make_this_information_visible_to_those_agents_that_need_the_external_ticket_number?"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Question:_I.E2.80.99m_using_Case_Exchange_to_exchange_Incidents_with_an_external_system._Agents_with_the_.E2.80.98Tenant_Admin.E2.80.99_role_can_see_the_information_on_the_exchanged_Incident.2C_but_other_users_can_not._How_do_I_make_this_information_visible_to_those_agents_that_need_the_external_ticket_number.3F">Question: I’m using Case Exchange to exchange Incidents with an external system. Agents with the ‘Tenant Admin’ role can see the information on the exchanged Incident, but other users can not. How do I make this information visible to those agents that need the external ticket number?</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=SMAX:2018.05/PractitionersNotes/SMAX_Config/cg_faq&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=9" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Question: I’m using Case Exchange to exchange Incidents with an external system. Agents with the ‘Tenant Admin’ role can see the information on the exchanged Incident, but other users can not. How do I make this information visible to those agents that need the external ticket number?">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=SMAX:2018.05/PractitionersNotes/SMAX_Config/cg_faq&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Question: I’m using Case Exchange to exchange Incidents with an external system. Agents with the ‘Tenant Admin’ role can see the information on the exchanged Incident, but other users can not. How do I make this information visible to those agents that need the external ticket number?">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Answer:_3">Answer:</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=SMAX:2018.05/PractitionersNotes/SMAX_Config/cg_faq&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=10" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Answer:">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=SMAX:2018.05/PractitionersNotes/SMAX_Config/cg_faq&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Answer:">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>Not every role has the ability to see this information in the out of the box system. However, it is possible to add this to any role in the system.
</p><p>First, determine the role or roles that need the right to see the external ticket information. Bring up the role in question in the UI, then:
</p>
<ol><li>Navigate to the ‘Record Type’ section and press ‘Add’ (on the right side of the screen)</li>
<li>On the newly displayed window, for the record type field, select ‘External Reference’</li>
<li>On the same form, check the box next to ‘View’</li>
<li>Press ‘Ok’</li>
<li>Save the role using the ‘Save’ button at the top of the screen</li></ol>

